        "content": "<p>Suppose I have a field F and an irreducible polynomial f(x) := x^2-a over F. Clearly, there exists an extension field K of F such that f has a root b := sqrt(a) in K satisfying f(b) = 0. But how can I express b and f(b) = 0 in Lean?</p>\n<p>Here's my code setup for variables:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">open</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Polynomial</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">variable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">F</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Field</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">F</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">variable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">F</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">noncomputable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">poly</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">F</span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">X</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">X</span><span class=\"bp\">^</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">C</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">variable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ha</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Irreducible</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">poly</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">))</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>I tried \\sqrt(a), but Lean showed an error. I also found roots, but this only applies to roots of f in F. I also found Complex.exists_root, but this requires embedding f into ℂ, especially embedding a into ℂ, and I don't know how to implement this.</p>\n<p>Is there a related solution in Lean's mathlib library?</p>",
